                  <persName id="t18320906-253-person2058">
                  GEORGE 
                  WYATT
               <interp inst="t18320906-253-person2058" type="surname" value="WYATT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-253-person2058" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-253-person2058" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18320906-253-viclabel1426" type="occupation">silk weaver</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-253-victim2056 t18320906-253-viclabel1426"></join>, and lodge on the ground floor at Benjamin Newley's, in <placeName id="t18320906-253-crimeloc1427">South-street, Bethnal-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-253-crimeloc1427" type="placeName" value="South-street, Bethnal-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-253-crimeloc1427" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-253-off1424 t18320906-253-crimeloc1427"></join> - the prisoner lodged in the same house, and is a silk weaver; he lodged up stairs in the workshop, and slept there. On the 31st of August I got up the about halfpast six o'clock in the morning, and went up to the workshop, where I had a considerable quantity of silk in the loom- it was entrusted to me by my employer; I am answerable for it - it is worth 7l. at least: I missed it, and the prisoner had left the house without giving any notice; I suspected him, and looked about for him - this was on Tuesday, and on the Monday I found him; I said, "George, you have got me into a pretty mess - I am likely to lose my bread;" a person said, "What has he done?" I said he had robbed me of sixty yards of silk; the prisoner replied "There were not sixty yards, it was between fifty and sixty, for I measured it."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-253-person2059">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  NEWLEY
               <interp inst="t18320906-253-person2059" type="surname" value="NEWLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-253-person2059" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-253-person2059" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a silk-weaver. I told the prisoner he had got me into a pretty mess, for our master suspected this was our own doing, and asked what he had done with it - he said he had pawned it; I went to the pawnbroker's by his direction, and found it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-253-person2060">
